Fetal diagnosis of atrioventricular septal defect with dextrocardia in trisomy 18. On prenatal ultrasound atrioventricular septal defect is often diagnosed in infants with Down syndrome based on an abnormal four-chamber view of the heart. A unique case of atrioventricular septal defect with dextroposition of the heart in an infant with trisomy 18 is presented.